Package komposten.leapjna.leapc.data

Class LEAP_DEVICE_INFO

java.lang.Object
com.sun.jna.Structure
komposten.leapjna.leapc.data.LEAP_DEVICE_INFO
@FieldOrder({"size","status","caps","pid","baseline","serial_length","serial","h_fov","v_fov","range"}) public class LEAP_DEVICE_INFO extends Structure

Properties of a Leap device.

Get a LEAP_DEVICE_INFO by calling LeapC.LeapGetDeviceInfo(Pointer, LEAP_DEVICE_INFO) with the handle for device. The device must be open.

Since:
LeapJna 1.0.0, Ultraleap Orion SDK 3.0.0

  • Field Details

    • size

      public int size
      Size of this structure.

    • status

      public int status
      A combination of eLeapDeviceStatus flags. Use getStatus() to get the status flags as an array of eLeapDeviceStatus values.

    • caps

      public int caps
      A combination of eLeapDeviceCaps flags. Use getCapabilities() to get the capabilities as an array of eLeapDeviceCaps values.

    • pid

      public int pid
      One of the eLeapDevicePID members. Use getPid() to get the product ID as an eLeapDevicePID value.

    • baseline

      public int baseline
      The device baseline, in micrometers. The baseline is defined as the distance between the center axis of each lens in a stereo camera system. For other camera systems, this value is set to zero.

    • serial_length

      public int serial_length
      The required length of the serial number char buffer including the null character.

    • serial

      public String serial
      A pointer to the null-terminated device serial number string.

    • h_fov

      public float h_fov
      The horizontal field of view of this device in radians.

    • v_fov

      The vertical field of view of this device in radians.

    • range

      The maximum range for this device, in micrometers.
